Post-Match Reflections: The last two games are exactly us.
We were a bit lucky at the start when Haaland hit the post, but even then we controlled the game.
The team's reaction was fantastic. What I particularly liked was that we never stopped.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria captain Marko Arnautovic (35) said his side are playing like their true selves again after they followed up last week's 4-0 win over Kazakhstan by thrashing Norway 5-1 in the Nations League on Sunday.
Austria are now tied on seven points with leaders Norway and Slovenia, with the side finishing top of the group earning direct promotion to Nations League A.
